parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking can cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward, potentially leading to accidents, especially when pulling out of parking lots or intersections.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward when the pedal finally engages
the problem occurs when driving or backing out of a parking lot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the MFS can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: turn signals only work off and on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire carrier rivets can cause the spare tire to become detached and fall off the vehicle, creating a road hazard and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: spare tire falls off the vehicle
